s fewer good chances against.", "method": "His suppression of 5v5 expected goals against, teammate- and competition-adjusted. Higher means fewer chances allowed while he's on the ice."}, "ppOffense": {"receipts": [{"label": "Power-play xG impact (RAPM)", "value": "+0.04 xG/60", "tone": "neutral", "strong": true}, {"label": "PP ice time", "value": "55 min", "tone": "neutral"}], "summary": "His impact on the POWER PLAY \u2014 how much his team's chances improve with him on the man advantage, graded only against players who actually log power-play minutes (so a bottom-six grinder isn't penalized for never being out there).", "method": "Power-play expected-goals impact, RAPM-adjusted. Graded vs peers who actually play the PP."}, "pkDefense": {"receipts": [{"label": "Penalty-kill xG suppression (RAPM)", "value": "+0.00 xG/60", "tone": "neutral", "strong": true}, {"label": "PK ice time", "value": "11 min", "tone": "neutral"}], "summary": "His impact on the PENALTY KILL \u2014 how well his team smothers chances while short-handed with him on the ice, graded against other penalty-killers.", "method": "Penalty-kill expected-goals suppression, RAPM-adjusted."}, "finishing": {"receipts": [{"label": "Career shots", "value": "173", "tone": "neutral"}, {"label": "Goals", "value": "6", "tone": "neutral"}, {"label": "Goals above cell-expected", "value": "+0.6", "tone": "pos"}, {"label": "Finishing / 100 shots", "value": "+0.00", "tone": "neutral", "strong": true}, {"label": "95% band", "value": "-1.93 \u2026 +1.92", "tone": "neutral"}, {"label": "Sample", "value": "thin", "tone": "neutral"}], "summary": "Whether he converts MORE than an average shooter at his position would on the same shots \u2014 with each shot priced by how league shooters actually convert its CONTEXT (danger band \u00d7 strength state \u00d7 rebound), not just its geometry. Trusted more the more he's shot; the band says how sure we are.", "method": "Goals minus cell-expected goals per 100 shots, centered within